<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407084>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Pseudoodes coelestinus Chaudoir, 1882 (A–C: Oodes coelestinus, holotype; D–E: Oodes viridissimus, holotype; F–G: female specimen, Malaysia, Long Láma). A, D: habitus and labels; B: left metepisternum and metacoxa (arrow shows lateral end of metacoxal basal sulcus); C: right mesotarsomeres; E: head and pronotum; F: mentum; G: prosternal process. Scale lines = 2 mm (Fig. A, D); = 1 mm (Figs B–C, E); = 0.5 mm (Figs F–G)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4407084/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4407086>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Pseudoodes coelestinus Chaudoir, 1882 (A: male specimen, Malaysia, Mulu National Park; B: male specimen, Malaysia, Kapit; C–D: female specimen, Malaysia, Mulu National Park).A: median lobe of aedeagus, left lateral view; B: same, dorsal view; C: left gonocoxite, ventral view; D: spermathecal complex and gonocoxites, ventral view. Scale lines = 0.5 mm (Figs A–B, D); = 0.2 mm (Fig. C)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4407086/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

